The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 SK Mitra resigns from Birla group

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 Mumbai, July 6: S.K. Mitra, who looked after the AV Birla groups financial services, has tendered his resignation.

 Confirming the resignation, sources said though Mitra was to retire after six months, he had put in his papers early. Observers of the group said in many ways, Mitra was a key figure in the groups financial services.

 In financial services, the group is largely into mutual funds and life insurance. There are plans, though at a preliminary stage, to enter general insurance. Mitra had said the group was planning to enter general insurance and that it had received enquiries on alliance from companies in the US, the UK and Canada. He had also said the groups life insurance venture Birla Sun Life Insurance Company was targeting a Rs 2,000-crore first premium income in 2007-08 against Rs 950 crore achieved in the previous fiscal.

 Birla Sun Life is a 74:26 joint venture between the group and Canadian major Sun Life Financial. As part of its plan to increase its market share in the life insurance segment, it wants to increase its branch network by at least 400 this fiscal from 137. 




